# SSLCommerz Payment Gateway Configuration

# Get these credentials from SSLCommerz:
# 1. Sign up at: https://developer.sslcommerz.com/registration/
# 2. Get Sandbox credentials from dashboard
# 3. For production, request live credentials after business verification

# Sandbox Credentials (for testing)
SSLCOMMERZ_STORE_ID=your_store_id_here
SSLCOMMERZ_STORE_PASSWORD=your_store_password_here

# Set to False for production
SSLCOMMERZ_IS_SANDBOX=True

# Example Sandbox Credentials (you need to get your own):
# SSLCOMMERZ_STORE_ID=testbox
# SSLCOMMERZ_STORE_PASSWORD=qwerty123

# How to get SSLCommerz credentials:
# 1. Go to https://developer.sslcommerz.com/
# 2. Click "Register" or "Sign Up"
# 3. Fill in your business details
# 4. Verify your email
# 5. Login to dashboard
# 6. Get Sandbox Store ID and Store Password from Integration section
# 7. Copy them here

# Test Card Numbers (Sandbox Mode Only):
# Visa: 4111 1111 1111 1111
# Mastercard: 5555 5555 5555 4444
# AMEX: 3782 822463 10005
# CVV: Any 3 digits
# Expiry: Any future date

# Mobile Banking Test Numbers (Sandbox):
# bKash: 01XXXXXXXXX (any valid BD number)
# Nagad: 01XXXXXXXXX (any valid BD number)
# Rocket: 01XXXXXXXXX (any valid BD number)

# Production Setup:
# 1. Change SSLCOMMERZ_IS_SANDBOX=False in settings.py
# 2. Get live credentials from SSLCommerz after business verification
# 3. Update SSLCOMMERZ_STORE_ID and SSLCOMMERZ_STORE_PASSWORD with live credentials
# 4. Test thoroughly before going live
